      <Content>The term ἀκροβυστία as a designation of a state of being uncircumcised belongs technically to a domain of physiological states (Domain 23). Since, however, its significance for the NT text is only in connection with the socio-religious character of people, ἀκροβυστία is classified here in Domain 11 Groups and Classes of Persons and Members of Such Groups and Classes  (see also {D:11.53}).</Content>
